review_blob: Fairly odourless.  Nice murky amber colour with a medium bubbly head.  Floral hoppy flavour with sweet touch.  Hops stay on the tongue.

Smells of chocolate and coffee, pours dark brown almost black with a nice head that disappears quickly.  Tastes strongly of chocolate with a hint of coffee, very bubbly on the tongue with a chocolaty bitter sweet finish.  Not bad, a bit heavy on the chocolate.
Pours a dark chestnut brown with a full head.  Kind of watery with hints of malt and smoke that turn to molasses on the tongue.  Not a great beer, doesnt have any real flavour, would not buy again.
Clear, light brown, not much head.  Very non  deScript smell.  Fizzy and slightly sweet on the tongue with a bitter finish that lasts on the tongue.
Pours a nice murky nut brown colour with a medium head.  Very hoppy with slight undertones of citrus.  Alcohol disappears quickly while the hops stay on the tongue for quite some time.  Solid IPA.
Nice head, clear and golden appearance.  Taste is quite skunky and kind of watery with the alcohol sitting on the palate.  Not a great beer, needs more uuumph.
Golden brown appearance with lots of carbonation and a foamy head.  Taste is bitter at first then finishes sweet fruity and sweet with a lingering palate.  Good beer, more hoppy than most Belgians.
Beautiful murky brown colour with a wonderful head.  Perfect blend of malt and hops, not to bitter and not overly sweet with a nice hint of caramel.  Cant taste the alcohol on finish.
Looks good in the glass, nice foamy head.  Hoppy with a hint of fruits and wheat.  Bitterness stays on the tongue for a long while.  Good tasting IPA, not the best but Id buy it again.

Looks fantastic in the glass, soft opaque brown with a murky texture.  Carbon explodes on the tongue with nice fruity undertones.  Alcohol disappears fast leaving a malty taste on the palate.  Great beer, one of my favourite Belgians.
Looks great in the glass.  Malt and ash taste.  Holds onto the palate with an ashy taste.  Good beer, I prefer something hoppier.
Nice hoppy dark ale.  Pours nicely, looks nice.  Bittersweet taste.  Bitter finish.
